cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes language inside the lyrics of songs using computational linguistic algorithms. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper involves predicting whether a song would make it to the top or bottom of the billboard rankings, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and predicting trends in the music industry. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category as the paper uses an SVM classifier with a radial kernel function to predict the rankings of songs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper involves using machine learning algorithms to analyze and predict trends in the music industry.
